Distance Aptitude	KEY:Trait ~ Distance Aptitude					SOURCEPAGE:p.19	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Distance Aptitude]				DESC:You were exposed to the magic of an elf gate, portal, or some other form of distance-spanning magic when you were young. This contact with ancient world-spanning magic has granted you insight into means to extend the range of your own spells. Treat your caster level as 1 higher for the purposes of determining the range of spells and spell-like abilities.
Domineering		KEY:Trait ~ Domineering						SOURCEPAGE:p.19	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Domineering]				DESC:When you were young, you attracted a group of devoted companions thanks to your impressive talent, and the experience inspired in you a powerfl self assurance and air of superiority. Your confdence is so strong that others fe el naturally compelled to fllow your commands. Choose one 1st-level enchantment spell you are capable of casting. The DC of that spell increases by 1.
