Fey Protection	KEY:Trait ~ Fey Protection					SOURCEPAGE:p.20	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Fey Protection]				DESC:Your birth brought an unexpected guest to your parents' home: a helpfl fy who prophesied about your future and gave you a magical gift in exchange for your parents' hospitality, a cup of milk, and a drop of your blood. You gain a +1 trait bonus to AC against attacks of opportunities made by fy and a +1 trait bonus on saving throws against the efects of fey creatures.
Fortunate		KEY:Trait ~ Fortunate						SOURCEPAGE:p.20	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Fortunate]				DESC:You are blessed by fate. Once per day when you use a spell or magic item with a randomized efect (such as corfusion, mirror ima1e, prismatic spray, or a ba1 of tricks), befre you roll to determine the result, you may choose to roll twice and pick either result.
Inured to Death	KEY:Trait ~ Inured to Death					SOURCEPAGE:p.20	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Inured to Death]				DESC:You have been around death or the undead all of your life; you have become accustomed to its shadowy presence, and are no longer overwhelmed by it. You gain a +2 trait bonus on saving throws against death efects.
Magical Flair	KEY:Trait ~ Magical Flair					SOURCEPAGE:p.20	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Magical Flair]				DESC:At a young age, you saw a witch burned by farfl peasants, druids flsely punished for demon worship, or another sort of spellcaster persecuted for merely practicing her dubious craf. Intent on not sufering the same fate, you approach spellcasting with a powerfl desire to control how your magic is perceived by others. You can cause spells you cast to manifest with strange visual, auditory, or olfactory features that make them hard to identify. Choose a school of magic. The Spellcraf DC to identify spells you cast fom that school of magic increases by 2. Onlookers who fil a Spellcraf check to identify your spell by 2 or less incorrectly identify the spell as another randomly selected spell of the same school and level.
Mutant Eye		KEY:Trait ~ Mutant Eye						SOURCEPAGE:p.20	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Mutant Eye]				DESC:One of your parents was exposed to uncontrolled magic or arcane pollution befre you were born, causing you to develop a minor mutation that has marked you as diferent all your life. You have a third eye on your frehead. As long as it is uncovered and open, you can get a clearer sense of the emotions of those you see, granting you a +2 trait bonus on Sense Motive checks that increases to +4 on checks to notice whether a character is under a mind-afecting efect. However, the eye is unsettling, and you take a -1 penalty on Bluf and Diplomacy checks against humanoids who can see it.
