Avid Reader			KEY:Trait ~ Avid Reader							SOURCEPAGE:p.20	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Avid Reader]				DESC:As a youth, you voraciously consumed books and scrolls provided by a member of an adventurer's guild or a learned organization like the Pathfnder Society, and you have internalized these stories of bold adventurers. Choose one Knowledge skill. You can always choose to take 10 on checks with the chosen Knowledge skill, even when distracted OT threatened.
Competitive			KEY:Trait ~ Competitive							SOURCEPAGE:p.21	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Competitive]				DESC:You grew up and were raised around fbulous sporting events, and your youth was consumed with a driving need to be better than everyone else. Any hint of a contest spurs you to your greatest heights of potential. Whenever another creature within 30 fet attempts a skill check and you attempt a check with the same skill befre the start of that creature's next turn, you gain a +1 trait bonus on your check (this includes attempting an opposed skill check against the creature).
Free Spirit			KEY:Trait ~ Free Spirit							SOURCEPAGE:p.21	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Free Spirit]				DESC:You respect the feedom of others to speak as they will. Your rough-and-tumble youth taught you that everyone deserves a chance to say her piece. After all, you can always simply choose to ignore the speaker. You gain a +1 trait bonus on saving throws against language­ dependent and efects with the sonic descriptor. In addition, the DC to Intimidate you increases by 2.
Friends in High Places	KEY:Trait ~ Friends in High Places					SOURCEPAGE:p.21	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Friends in High Places]				DESC:You have ofen seen lawbreakers go fee when they demonstrate they have fiends in high places, and so you put special effrt into befiending powerfl people yourself Whenever you are in an area in which you have used the Diplomacy skill to gather infrmation, you gain a +1 trait bonus on Diplomacy and Intimidate checks. This bonus increases to +2 when dealing with government officials.
Gregarious			KEY:Trait ~ Gregarious							SOURCEPAGE:p.21	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Gregarious]				DESC:At least once in your childhood, your fmily moved for a reason you didn't understand and you were frced to leave behind your old fiends and make new ones. Ever since, you have always been the frst to meet strangers, make new fiends, and welcome travelers. You learned that frst impressions are the most important, and have a knack for making a good one. Once per day, when you attempt a Diplomacy check to improve a creature's attitude toward you, you may choose to reroll the check after the frst roll is made but befre the results are revealed. You must take the second result, even ifit is worse.
Grim Optimism		KEY:Trait ~ Grim Optimism						SOURCEPAGE:p.21	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Grim Optimism]				DESC:Growing up with no one to rely on but yourself you learned to keep a realistic view of your situation and avoid flling into the trap of cynicism with a healthy dose of wit. As a standard action, you can joke about a troublesome situation to lighten the load of dealing with it for yourself and others. You and all allies within 30 fet who can hear you gain a +2 morale bonus on saving throws against fear and pain efects for ld4 rounds. A character cannot benefit fom this efect more than once in 24 hours.
Memorable			KEY:Trait ~ Memorable							SOURCEPAGE:p.21	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Memorable]				DESC:Growing up amid a large number of children, you learned quickly how to get others' attention and keep it. When you modify a character's attitude with the Diplomacy or Intimidate skill, the attitude change lasts 1-1/2 times longer than it otherwise would. Whenever you create a fear or mind-afecting efect that imposes a penalty or bonus with a duration of at least 2 rounds, it lasts 1 additional round afer it would normally end. For example, if you demoralize a fe with an Intimidate check and beat the DC by 5, the victim is shaken for 3 rounds instead of the usual 2 rounds.
Secret-Keeper		KEY:Trait ~ Secret-Keeper						SOURCEPAGE:p.21	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Secret-Keeper]				DESC:Growing up in a land where paranoia flls the air and any accusation of heresy or dissent can spell doom for whole fmilies, you learned very quickly to keep a secret. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Bluf checks and a +1 trait bonus on saving throws against divinations, domination efects, and efects that would compel you to speak the truth.
Snowbound			KEY:Trait ~ Snowbound							SOURCEPAGE:p.21	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Snowbound]				DESC:You came of age in a place with harsh winters amid a culture that rewarded you for testing your limits in the cold. You gain a +1 trait bonus on saving throws against cold efects and a +2 trait bonus on Fortitude saves against the efects of cold weather.
Student of Philosophy	KEY:Trait ~ Student of Philosophy					SOURCEPAGE:p.21	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Student of Philosophy]				DESC:You were trained in a now­ defnct philosophical tradition-such as that of the now­ destroyed Gaitan universities or Lirgeni astrologers-and learned to use logic and reason to persuade others. You can use your Intelligence modifer in place of your Charisma modifer on Diplomacy checks to persuade others and on Bluf checks to convince others that a lie is true. (This trait does not afect Diplomacy checks to gather infrmation or Bluf checks to fe int in combat.)
